$ R: working directory

The *working directory* specifies the location where file operations (i.e. wrting and reading) take place by default (that is: without specifying an
absolute path). Among such functions are
  → development/languages/R/functions/list_files[`list.files()`], 
  → development/languages/R/functions/getwd[`getwd()`],
  → development/languages/R/functions/setwd[`setwd()`] etc.

The working directory is set with development/languages/R/functions/setwd[setwd] and inquired about with → development/languages/R/functions/getwd[getwd].
